full_text: Screened by NARA, 6/7/2023 TRANSLATION 1267899 CERTIFICATION The undersigned clerk in charge of the OFFICE OF THE REGISTRAR OF VITAL STATISTICS CERTIFIES: That in the archives of births in this office in docket No 0501- 42-00352 located in folio 265, liber 78 for the year 1942 it is literally stated: JUANA ALVARADO ROMERO. - In San Pedro Sula, at 2:30 in the afternoon on Friday, March 6, 1942 Before me Guillermo Lopez Rodezno, Secretary of the Council of this district and Registrar of Vital Statistics and before the witnesses Elba Rodriguez B. and J, Alfredo Cote, adults, Hundurans and domiciliaries appeared SECUNDINO ALVARADO, adult, single, Salvadorean who declared that on Saturday, 28th day of the past month, at 10 p.m. in Mapala of this district, there was born a female child given the name of "JUANA". The natural daughter of and acknowledged by the declarant and Transito Romero, adult, single, Hondurans and of this community. The paternal grandparents are: RUPERTO ALVARDO and CIPRIANA BONILLA and maternal grandparents are JULIAN ROMERO and SANTOS ALVARADO. The foregoing was read to, ratified but not signed due to being illiterate. No marginal notes. Issued in San Pedro Sula, Cortes, on January 31, 1989. Signed JOSE NAPOLION JIMINEZ, REGISTRAR I the undersigned, an attorney in this state affirm that I am familiar with and have knowledge of both English and Spanish languages and that the foregoing is a true and complete English translation of the original in Spanish. april 18, 1989 Vincent Sexaci Vincent Geraci
